(1, 'Arborvitae Essential Oil', 32.00, 'Essential Oil', '2024-04-14 14:38:14', '2024-04-14 14:38:14', 'Arborvitae essential oil comes from the majestic arborvitae tree—also known as the western redcedar, Thuja plicata, and the tree of life that is native to Canada and the Northwestern US. Arborvitae essential oil captures the tree’s distinct, methyl thujate–rich chemical profile, providing a warm and earthy aroma that’s ideal for meditation. It’s also an effective cleaner for both the skin and household surfaces.', '5 mL', 'oil_arborvitae_thumb.png', 'oil_arborvitae_01.png,oil_arborvitae_02.png,oil_arborvitae_03.png', '- Arborvitae essential oil may promote clear, healthy-looking skin when applied topically, according to preclinical research\r\n- Arborvitae oil serves as a powerful cleansing agent\r\n- Arborvitae essential oil provides a warm, earthy aroma', '- Add a few drops of Arborvitae essential oil to a spray bottle with water and spray on surfaces or hands for a quick DIY cleaner.\r\n- Apply Arborvitae essential oil to wrists and ankles while hiking or enjoying other outdoor activities for a pleasant aroma.\r\n- Diffuse Arborvitae essential oil to freshen the air.\r\n- Mix four drops of Arborvitae oil with two drops of Lemon essential oil in 6 ounces of water for a natural wood polish.\r\n- Diffuse Arborvitae essential oil or apply during mediation to create a peaceful, calming atmosphere.', 'Aromatic use: Add three to four drops of Arborvitae essential oil in the diffuser of choice.\r\nTopical use: Apply one to two drops of Arborvitae essential oil to desired area. Dilute with a carrier oil to minimize any skin sensitivity. See additional precautions below.', 'Possible skin sensitivity. Keep out of reach of children. If you are pregnant, nursing, or under a doctor’s care, consult your physician. Avoid contact with eyes, inner ears, and sensitive areas.'),
(2, 'Basil Essential Oil', 44.00, 'Essential Oil', '2024-04-14 14:42:55', '2024-04-14 14:42:55', 'A staple in Thai and Italian cuisine and a delicious addition to tomato soup, basil is a popular plant in many herb gardens. The sweet, warm, and spicy flavor of Basil essential oil is perfect for your culinary ventures.', '15 mL', 'oil_basil_thumb.png', 'oil_basil_01.png,oil_basil_02.png,oil_basil_03.png', '- Basil oil provides a calming, relaxing aroma.\r\n- Basil essential oil offers soothing comfort when incorporated into a massage.\r\n- Basil essential oil may support a healthy cell lifecycle when used internally, according to preclinical research.\r\n- Basil oil provides added cleansing power to surface cleaners.', '- Diffuse Basil essential oil as part of a study or work routine.\r\n- Apply Basil essential oil to the skin with a carrier oil and include as part of a soothing massage.\r\n- Add Basil oil to your favorite Italian dishes for a refreshing taste.', 'Aromatic use: Place three to four drops of Basil essential oil in the diffuser of your choice.\r\n\r\nInternal Use: Add one drop to four fluid ounces of liquid.\r\n\r\nTopical use: Apply one to two drops of Basil essential oil to the desired area. Dilute with a carrier oil to minimize any skin sensitivity.', 'Possible skin sensitivity. Keep out of reach of children. If you’re pregnant, nursing, or under a doctor’s care, consult your physician. Avoid contact with eyes, inner ears, and sensitive areas.'),
(3, 'Bergamot Essential Oil', 57.33, 'Essential Oil', '2024-04-14 14:46:57', '2024-04-14 14:46:57', 'Bergamot essential oil is unique among citrus oils because it can create both an uplifting and calming environment. It may also support a healthy nervous system, calm the digestive system, and promote a healthy metabolism when taken internally thanks to limonene, one of its primary chemical constituents.\r\n\r\nBergamot is the most delicate citrus plant, requiring a special climate and soil to thrive. Italians have used bergamot oil for years to soothe and rejuvenate the skin. In Greece, unripe fruits are used as sweetmeats, which are eaten by the spoonful as dessert or with coffee.', '15 mL', 'oil_bergamot_thumb.png', 'oil_bergamot_01.png,oil_bergamot_02.png,oil_bergamot_03.png', '- Bergamot essential oil provides a calming and uplifting aroma.\r\n- Bergamot essential oil may support a healthy nervous system when taken internally because of the chemical component limonene.\r\n- Bergamot oil may calm the digestive system and promote a healthy metabolism when consumed because of the limonene content.', '- Diffuse Bergamot essential oil in the classroom, at work, or at home.\r\n- Apply Bergamot essential oil to the skin while showering and inhale deeply.\r\n- Add Bergamot oil to regular tea to transform it into Earl Grey.\r\n- Place a few drops of Bergamot essential oil in warm water for a relaxing foot soak.', 'Aromatic use: Add three to four drops of Bergamot essential oil to the diffuser of your choice.\r\nInternal use: Dilute one drop of Bergamot essential oil in 4 fluid ounces of liquid.\r\nTopical use: Apply one to two drops of Bergamot oil to desired area. Dilute with a carrier oil to minimize any skin sensitivity. See additional precautions below.', 'Possible skin sensitivity. Keep out of reach of children. If you are pregnant, nursing, or under a doctor’s care, consult your physician. Avoid contact with eyes, inner ears, and sensitive areas. Avoid sunlight and UV rays for at least 12 hours after applying product.'),
(4, 'Birch Essential Oil', 78.67, 'Essential Oil', '2024-04-14 14:49:25', '2024-04-14 14:49:25', 'Birch essential oil comes from the bark of Betula lenta tree—also known as black birch, cherry birch, or sweet birch. With its crisp, minty aroma, Birch oil promotes a stimulating and uplifting environment when diffused. You can apply it topically to help maintain a healthy-looking complexion.\r\n\r\nSourcing pure, unadulterated Birch essential oil is difficult, so historically it’s only been available in small volumes. After a long time diligently searching, doTERRA has partnered with a Pennsylvanian family to sustainably produce pure Birch essential oil. This family has even kept generational records of their expertise, making it possible to offer Birch permanently.', '5 mL', 'oil_birch_thumb.png', 'oil_birch_01.png,oil_birch_02.png,oil_birch_03.png', '- Birch essential oil delivers a stimulating, refreshing aroma reminiscent of Wintergreen.\r\n- Birch essential oil contributes to a soothing massage.\r\n- Birch oil promotes healthy-looking skin.', '- Massage Birch essential oil into the back and legs for a cooling sensation after exercise.\r\n- Place a few drops of Birch essential oil on a cotton ball and tuck it in your gym bag to mask odors.\r\n- Apply Birch essential oil to the skin to help reduce the appearance of blemishes.', 'Aromatic use:Add three to four drops of Birch essential oil to the diffuser of your choice.\r\n\r\nTopical Use:Apply one to two drops of Birch oil to the desired area. Dilute with a carrier oil to minimize any skin sensitivity.', 'Not for internal use. Possible skin sensitivity. Keep out of reach of children. If you’re pregnant, nursing, or under a doctor’s care, consult your physician. Avoid contact with eyes, inner ears, and sensitive areas.'),
(5, 'Black Pepper', 30.67, 'Essential Oil', '2024-04-14 14:53:54', '2024-04-14 14:53:54', 'Monoterpene- and sesquiterpene-rich Black Pepper enhances the flavor of nearly any dish. Its antioxidant properties help protect against environmental and seasonal threats when used internally. Black Pepper also supports digestion and healthy circulation when ingested. When diluted and applied topically, it contributes to a warming massage.', '5 mL', 'oil_black_pepper_thumb.png', 'oil_black_pepper_01.png,oil_black_pepper_02.png,oil_black_pepper_03.png', '- Provides antioxidant and digestive support when used internally.\r\n- Supports healthy circulation.\r\n- Enhances flavor.\r\n- Provides a soothing, satisfying aroma.', '- Create a warming, soothing massage by combining one to two drops with a carrier oil.\r\n- Use internally to help soothe and support the nervous system.\r\n- Take one to two drops in a Veggie Cap to support healthy cellular function.\r\n- Add to meats, soups, entrées, and salads to enhance flavor and aid digestion.', 'Aromatic Use: Place three to four drops in the diffuser of your choice.\r\n\r\nInternal Use: Add one drop to four fluid ounces of liquid.\r\n\r\nTopical Use: Apply one to two drops to the desired area. Dilute with a carrier oil to minimize any skin sensitivity.', 'Possible skin sensitivity. Keep out of reach of children. If you’re pregnant, nursing, or under a doctor’s care, consult your physician. Avoid contact with eyes, inner ears, and sensitive areas.'),
(6, 'Black Spruce Oil', 28.00, 'Essential Oil', '2024-04-14 14:55:41', '2024-04-14 14:55:41', 'A powerful wood oil, Black Spruce is steam-distilled from the needles and branches of the Picea mariana tree. With a history of use by Native Americans to promote skin health, it’s the perfect addition to a cleansing skincare routine.\r\n\r\nBlack Spruce contains high amounts of the chemical constituent bornyl acetate, which provides a calming aroma. Diffuse it or apply it to the back of the neck throughout the day to enjoy a relaxing sensation and promote feelings of clear airways and easy breathing. Black Spruce also features a cooling, soothing sensation when applied topically. Dilute it with a carrier and massage it into the skin or tired muscles for a comforting massage.', '5 mL', 'oil_black_spruce_thumb.png', 'oil_black_spruce_01.png,oil_black_spruce_02.png,oil_black_spruce_03.png', '- Soothes tired muscles.\r\n- Provides a calming, relaxing aroma.\r\n- Promotes feelings of clear airways and easy breathing.\r\n- Soothes minor skin irritations.', '- Combine with carrier oil and massage into the skin for soothing comfort.\r\n- Diffuse throughout the day for a relaxing aroma.\r\n- Apply to the skin to help soothe minor skin irritations.\r\n- Inhale throughout the day to promote feelings of easy breathing.', 'Aromatic use:Place three to four drops in the diffuser of your choice.\r\n\r\nTopical use:Apply one to two drops to the desired area. Dilute with a carrier oil to minimize any skin sensitivity.', 'Possible skin sensitivity. Keep out of reach of children. If you’re pregnant, nursing, or under a doctor’s care, consult your physician. Avoid contact with eyes, inner ears, and sensitive areas.'),
(7, 'Blue Lotus Touch', 88.00, 'Essential Oil', '2024-04-14 14:57:50', '2024-04-14 14:57:50', 'Blue lotus, also known as the water lily, is a majestic blue flower with a vibrant yellow center. It represents long life, health, honor, and good luck. It was considered by ancient Egyptians to be a sacred and even magical flower. The blossoms were sprinkled over King Tut’s body before he was entombed.\r\n\r\nBlue Lotus Touch can be used in a massage, as a meditation aid, and for overall skin hydration. It also makes for an enchanting personal fragrance.\r\n\r\nBlue lotus grows best in small ponds with high humidity. Sourced in Asia, the rare blossoms are collected by local families early in the morning when the delicate petals are fully open to the sun. Thanks to a Co-Impact Sourcing® partnership, more than 85 farmers can now make a living and raise families by growing and harvesting flowers used in Blue Lotus Touch.', '10 mL', 'oil_blue_lotus_touch_thumb.png', 'oil_blue_lotus_touch_01.png,oil_blue_lotus_touch_02.png,oil_blue_lotus_touch_03.png', '- Provides a relaxing floral aroma.\r\n- Serves as a natural skin moisturizer.\r\n- Promotes a healthy-looking, radiant complexion.', '- Apply to the pulse points for a centering, relaxing aroma throughout the day.\r\n- Use as part of a daily skincare routine to help maintain the skin’s natural moisture barrier.\r\n- Roll on the neck and wrists for a tranquil, calming personal aroma.', 'Topical Use: Apply to the desired area as needed—no dilution required.', 'Possible skin sensitivity. Keep out of reach of children. If you’re pregnant, nursing, or under a doctor’s care, consult your physician. Avoid contact with eyes, inner ears, and sensitive areas.'),
(8, 'Turmeric Oil', 46.67, 'Essential Oil', '2024-04-14 15:01:51', '2024-04-14 15:01:51', 'A key botanical in traditional Indian Ayurvedic health practices, turmeric root and oil have a long history that’s inspired modern uses. Steam-distilled from the root, Turmeric essential oil has two unique chemical components: turmerone and ar-Turmerone. Most known for their nervous system benefits, these components make using Turmeric internally a staple in your daily health routine.*\r\n\r\nTurmeric essential oil is beneficial however you use it—internally, topically, or aromatically. Advantageous to the immune system, ingested Turmeric may have soothing benefits that promote a positive immune response and healthy circulation.* Turmeric can help promote clear, smooth, and radiant-looking skin. It also serves as a great burst of flavor in your favorite savory meals and offers a warm, spicy, and earthy aroma when diffused.', '15 mL', 'oil_turmeric_thumb.png', 'oil_turmeric_01.png,oil_turmeric_02.png,oil_turmeric_03.png', '- Helps support healthy glucose and lipid metabolism when taken internally.\r\n- May enhance cellular antioxidant enzymes (like glutathione) when taken internally.\r\n- May support healthy nervous and cellular function when taken internally.\r\n- Increases curcumin potency and absorption when taken internally.\r\n- May promote healthy immune function and response when consumed.\r\n- Supports clean and healthy-looking skin, while also reducing the appearance of blemishes.', '- Take internally for daily antioxidant support and to improve immune response.\r\n- Use internally for metabolic support when trying to get back on track.\r\n- Use as a spot treatment or a face mask to help reduce the appearance of blemishes or for a healthy-looking overall glow.\r\n- Diffuse for a warm, spicy, and earthy aroma.\r\n- Incorporate into your recovery routine as part of a soothing massage after strenuous activity.', 'Aromatic use: Place three to four drops in the diffuser of your choice.\r\nInternal use: Dilute one drop in four fluid ounces of liquid.\r\nTopical use: Apply one to two drops to the desired area. Dilute with a carrier oil to minimize any skin sensitivity. See additional precautions below.', 'Possible skin sensitivity. Keep out of reach of children. If you are pregnant, nursing or under a doctor\'s care, consult your physician. Avoid contact with eyes, inner ears, and sensitive areas.'),
(9, 'Ylang Ylang Oil', 58.67, 'Essential Oil', '2024-04-14 15:04:08', '2024-04-14 15:04:08', 'Ylang Ylang essential oil is derived from the star-shaped flowers of the tropical Ylang Ylang tree and is used extensively in making perfumes and in aromatherapy. Similar to Jasmine, Ylang Ylang has been used for centuries in religious and wedding ceremonies. In aromatherapy, Ylang Ylang is used to create a calm, positive atmosphere. Ylang Ylang is frequently used in luxurious hair and skin products for its scent and nourishing and protective properties. Taken internally, Ylang Ylang provides antioxidant support.* Ylang Ylang essential oil blends well with Bergamot, Geranium, Grapefruit, and Vetiver.', '15 mL', 'oil_ylang_ylang_thumb.png', 'oil_ylang_ylang_01.png,oil_ylang_ylang_02.png,oil_ylang_ylang_03.png', '- Provides antioxidant support when used internally.\r\n- Promotes a calming, positive atmosphere.', '- Combine a few drops with Epsom salts and use in warm water for a relaxing bath.\r\n- Use in a steam facial to refresh skin.\r\n- Put on wrists for a sweet, floral perfume.\r\n- Mix with a carrier oil for a deep hair conditioner.', 'Aromatic use: Add three to four drops to the diffuser of choice.\r\nInternal use: Dilute one drop in four fluid ounces of liquid.\r\nTopical use: Apply one to two drops to desired area. Dilute with a carrier oil to minimize any skin sensitivity. See additional precautions below.', 'Possible skin sensitivity. Keep out of reach of children. If you are pregnant, nursing, or under a doctor’s care, consult your physician. Avoid contact with eyes, inner ears, and sensitive areas.'),
(10, 'Peppermint Touch', 28.00, 'Essential Oil', '2024-04-14 15:10:26', '2024-04-14 15:10:26', 'doTERRA Touch Peppermint contains Peppermint essential oil and Fractionated Coconut Oil to provide a multitude of benefits. Its minty, fresh scent can be used aromatically and topically throughout the day to uplift mood and promote a sense of focus. Peppermint essential oil is known to lessen feelings of tension when applied to the temples or the back of the neck. doTERRA Touch Peppermint can be applied to these areas and anywhere on the body to provide a cooling massage or to naturally deter insects.\r\n\r\n', '10 mL', 'oil_peppermint_thumb.png', 'oil_peppermint_01.png,oil_peppermint_02.png,oil_peppermint_03.png', '- Helps lessen feelings of tension\r\n- Uplifts mood and promotes a sense of focus\r\n- Repels insects naturally', '- Rub on temples when waking for a refreshing morning boost.\r\n- Massage onto back of neck for a cooling sensation and to relieve feelings of tension.\r\n- Apply to skin for a cooling effect.', 'Topical Use: Apply to desired area. See additional precautions below.', 'Possible skin sensitivity. Keep out of reach of children. If pregnant or under a doctor’s care, consult your physician. Avoid contact with eyes, inner ears, and sensitive areas.'),
(11, 'Tangerine Essential Oil', 21.33, 'Essential Oil', '2024-04-14 15:13:03', '2024-04-14 15:13:03', 'Tangerine essential can brighten any space with its sweet, tangy aroma. Preclinical research suggests it may aid in healthy digestion and metabolism when consumed because of its rich limonene content.\r\n\r\nThe elevated limonene content in CPTG Certified Pure Tested Grade® Tangerine oil sets it apart as a superior surface cleaner. Tangerine also enhances the taste of desserts, beverages, and other recipes that call for citrus.', '15 mL', 'oil_tangerine_thumb.png', 'oil_tangerine_01.png,oil_tangerine_02.png,oil_tangerine_03.png', '- May help maintain healthy digestion and metabolism when used internally, but additional confirming research is needed.\r\n- Effectively cleans surfaces.\r\n- Delivers a refreshing, invigorating, and elevating aroma.', '- Add a few drops of Tangerine essential to your favorite diffuser or rub it into your hands and inhale.\r\n- Use Tangerine oil to enhance the flavor in cake or cookie recipes.\r\n- Add a drop or two of Tangerine essential oil to water, tea, or lemonade to boost the flavor.', 'Aromatic use: Place three to four drops of Tangerine essential oil in the diffuser of your choice.\r\n\r\nInternal Use: Dilute one drop of Tangerine oil in four fluid ounces of liquid.\r\n\r\nTopical use: Apply one to two drops of Tangerine essential oil to the desired area. Dilute with a carrier oil to minimize any skin sensitivity.', 'Possible skin sensitivity. Keep out of reach of children. If you’re pregnant, nursing, or under a doctor’s care, consult your physician. Avoid contact with eyes, inner ears, face, and sensitive areas. Avoid sunlight and UV rays for at least 12 hours after applying the product.'),
(12, 'Clary Sage Essential Oil', 52.00, 'Essential Oil', '2024-04-14 15:15:07', '2024-04-14 15:15:07', 'Clary sage is a biennial or perennial herb that grows up to six feet in height. In the Middle Ages, the plant was frequently used to soothe the skin. Clary Sage essential oil is known for its calming properties and skin benefits.\r\n\r\nThe main chemical component of Clary Sage oil is linalyl acetate—part of the esters group—making it one of the most relaxing, soothing, and balancing essential oils. Inhaling Clary Sage essential oil adds to a relaxing environment, and taking it internally promotes a restful night’s sleep.', '15 mL', 'oil_clary_sage_thumb.png', 'oil_clary_sage_01.png,oil_clary_sage_02.png,oil_clary_sage_03.png', '- Promotes healthy-looking hair and scalp\r\n- Supports a restful night’s sleep when taken internally\r\n- Calms and soothes the skin', '- Rub three to five drops on abdomen for a soothing massage.\r\n- Add Clary Sage essential oil to bathwater for a soothing bath.\r\n- Mix Clary Sage essential oil with shampoo or hair conditioner to promote healthy hair and scalp.\r\n- Combine with a carrier oil to massage, soothe, or rejuvenate skin.', 'Aromatic use:Place three to four drops in the diffuser of your choice.\r\n\r\nInternal Use:Dilute one drop in four fluid ounces of liquid.\r\n\r\nTopical use:Apply one to two drops to the desired area. Dilute with a carrier oil to minimize any skin sensitivity.', 'Possible skin sensitivity. Keep out of reach of children. If you’re pregnant, nursing, or under a doctor’s care, consult your physician. Avoid contact with eyes, inner ears, and sensitive areas.\r\n\r\n'),
(13, 'Juniper Berry Essential Oil', 30.67, 'Essential Oil', '2024-04-14 15:18:09', '2024-04-14 15:18:09', 'Woody, fresh, and crisp, CPTG Certified Pure Tested Grade® Juniper Berry Essential Oil has a calming and grounding aroma.\r\n\r\nJuniper berries have been used for centuries in cleansing and purifying rituals, as well as meditation practices. Their use can be traced to Old Testament times.\r\n\r\nJuniper Berry essential oil is high in ?-Pinene, which might contribute antioxidant properties when used internally, according to preclinical research.\r\n\r\nJuniper Berry oil serves as an invigorating addition to diffuser blends, revitalizing massages, skincare products, and natural cleaning supplies.', '5 mL', 'oil_juniper_berry_thumb.png', 'oil_juniper_berry_01.png,oil_juniper_berry_02.png,oil_juniper_berry_03.png', '- Juniper Berry essential oil may provide antioxidant properties when consumed, according to preclinical studies.\r\n- Juniper Berry oil may have cleansing properties. \r\n- Juniper Berry essential oil may support a healthy metabolism, according to preclinical research.\r\n- Juniper Berry essential oil has a calming, grounded aroma. ', '- Mix a few drops of Juniper Berry essential oil with Fractionated Coconut Oil for an energizing massage. \r\n- Add one drop of Juniper Berry oil to a facial cleanser or moisturizer to promote a clear, healthy-looking complexion. \r\n- Diffuse Juniper Berry essential oil to freshen the air. ', 'Aromatic use: Place three to four drops of Juniper Berry essential oil in the diffuser of your choice.\r\n\r\nInternal Use: Dilute one of Juniper Berry oil drop in four fluid ounces of liquid.\r\n\r\nTopical use: Apply one to two drops of Juniper Berry essential oil to the desired area. Dilute with a carrier oil to minimize any skin sensitivity.', 'Possible skin sensitivity, Keep out of reach of children. If you’re pregnant, nursing, or under a doctor’s care, consult your physician. Avoid contact with eyes, inner ears, and sensitive areas.'),
(14, 'Vetiver Essential Oil', 88.00, 'Essential Oil', '2024-04-14 15:20:05', '2024-04-14 15:20:05', 'Vetiver essential oil is sourced from a sturdy member of the grass family. Unlike other grasses, vetiver roots grow down, preventing erosion and stabilizing the soil.\r\n\r\nVetiver oil has a rich, grounding, and exotic aroma that’s popular in perfumery and massage therapy. Rub Vetiver essential oil on the bottoms of the feet before bedtime as you prepare for a restful night’s sleep.', '15 mL', 'oil_vetiver_thumb.png', 'oil_vetiver_01.png,oil_vetiver_02.png,oil_vetiver_03.png', '- Vetiver essential oil provides a calming, grounding aroma. \r\n- Vetiver oil adds to a relaxing massage. ', '- Incorporate Vetiver essential oil into a relaxing massage. \r\n- Take a warm bath, adding a few drops of Vetiver oil for a calming scent. ', 'Aromatic use: Place three to four drops of Vetiver essential oil in the diffuser of your choice.\r\n\r\nInternal Use: Add one drop of Vetiver oil to four fluid ounces of liquid.\r\n\r\nTopical use: Apply one to two drops of Vetiver essential oil to the desired area. Dilute with a carrier oil to minimize any skin sensitivity.', 'Possible skin sensitivity, Keep out of reach of children. If you’re pregnant, nursing, or under a doctor’s care, consult your physician. Avoid contact with eyes, inner ears, and sensitive areas.');

